desks. Place it on the floor.\n- Add a large rectangular whiteboard on the front wall, positioned above and behind the teacher\'s desk.\n- Create four walls enclosing the classroom, with smooth corners and a door on one side wall.\n- Create a floor matching the size to fit all objects comfortably with no collisions.\n- Add multiple ceiling lights evenly distributed for ample lighting.\n- Include a tall bookshelf filled with books along one side wall.\n- Put educational posters and charts spaced on the side and back walls.\n- Add a large window with curtains on the opposite side wall from the bookshelf.\n- Place a wall clock on a side wall visible to everyone.\n- Add a potted plant in a corner to add greenery.\n- Include waste bins near the teacher\'s desk and at the back of the classroom.\n- Use a warm wood tone for the student desks, a darker wood tone for the teacher\'s desk, and complementary colors for the chairs.\n- Color the walls in a light neutral color and the floor in a slightly darker hue for contrast.\n- Ensure all chairs face the front, teacher desk and chair face the students.\n- Make sure there is enough walking space between desks and no collisions among
